cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing an intelligent anti-malware system using deep learning models. It falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with malware detection and classification. The paper extensively uses deep learning models such as CNN, GRU, and MLP, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The dataset used in the paper consists of malware images, which requires computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for processing. Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the deep learning models, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
